topic: Telix to Participate in UBS and Jefferies Global Healthcare Conferences

ideas.title: Telix's Coffee Run
ideas.premise: Telix execs, jetlagged after the conference, order ridiculously specific Melbourne coffees, confusing baristas at Flinders Street Station.
ideas.why_funny: Relatable to Melburnians; highlights finance people's fussy coffee habits.

ideas.title: K-Pop vs. Healthcare
ideas.premise: Diljit Dosanjh, Twice, and a Telix CEO accidentally end up at the wrong conferences due to bad GPS.
ideas.why_funny: Juxtaposition of healthcare seriousness and K-pop/Bollywood fandom absurdity.

ideas.title: UBS and Jefferies: The Musical
ideas.premise: A flock of ibis are singing about Telix like they are in a broadway style play on St. Kilda pier.
ideas.why_funny: Ibises are very recognizable Melbourne animals, singing financial jargon is amusing.

ideas.title: The Great Southern Bio-way
ideas.premise: Telix execs get lost on the Great Ocean Road, mistaking scenic lookouts for valuable biotechnology hubs.
ideas.why_funny: Pokes fun at over-optimism and geographical confusion.

ideas.title: Hook Turn Healthcare
ideas.premise: Telix presentation is a visual representation of Melbourne's hook turns, complex and confusing for overseas investors.
ideas.why_funny: Hook turns are uniquely Melburnian and often baffling; comparing them to finance is funny.
